<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 08 at 6:05PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern
Sampson, southern Harnett, Cumberland and southwestern Johnston
Counties through 700 PM EDT...
At 605 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Pope AFB, or near Fort Bragg, moving east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Fayetteville, Lillington, Fort Bragg, Dunn, Benson, Godwin, Pope AFB,
Hope Mills, Spring Lake and Erwin.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
